  <!-- Overview -->
  <section id="overview">
    <h2>What is Pinochle?</h2>
    <p>Pinochle is a classic American trick-taking card game played with a 48-card deck (two copies of each card A, 10, K, Q, J, 9 in all four suits). It combines bidding, card combinations (meld), and trick-taking into one of the most strategic card games ever invented.</p>
    <p>Pinochle is especially popular in the Midwest and among players who grew up in the mid-20th century. It rewards card memory, partnership communication, and strategic bidding.</p>
